  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The preprint titled \"Imaging the voltage of neurons distributed across entire brains of larval zebrafish\" has made a noteworthy impact on the academic community, as evidenced by its 10 citations in various leading journals, including Nature Methods and Nature Communications. This research originated from esteemed institutions such as the Howard Hughes Medical Institute and the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, highlighting the quality and credibility of the work.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The preprint \"Imaging the voltage of neurons distributed across entire brains of larval zebrafish,\" published in 2023 on bioRxiv, has garnered significant academic attention, reflected in its 10 citations across reputable venues like Nature Methods and Nature Communications. This influence underscores the research's relevance and the high interest in advanced imaging techniques in neuroscience.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Contributed by a team affiliated with leading institutions such as the Howard Hughes Medical Institute and the McGovern Institute for Brain Research at MIT, this work benefits from strong institutional support, which bolsters its credibility and potential impact in the field of brain research. Additionally, the research's intersection with cutting-edge imaging technologies situates it at the forefront of scientific inquiry into neuronal activity, particularly in model organisms like larval zebrafish.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The data generated from this work has proven valuable for subsequent research, as indicated by its record of 11 instances of downstream reuse. This suggests that the methodologies or findings are being integrated into further studies, facilitating advancements in our understanding of neuronal dynamics. Although the work has no formal funding backing, the institutional affiliations provide a solid foundation for the research's validity and significance.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">While there are no public mentions or high-fidelity discourse indicators, the academic reception of this preprint is promising. The absence of any risk or credibility alerts and the lack of any non-supportive citations indicate a positive trajectory for this research area, emphasizing its contribution to ongoing discussions and studies in the field of neuroscience.</p>",
